{"type":"message","id":"1db9abc6","parentId":"f080906a","timestamp":"2026-03-27T07:10:34.070Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Okay, the user wants to create a product selector agent quickly. I tried using sessions_spawn with mode=\"session\" and runtime=\"acp\" but got an error saying mode=\"session\" requires thread=true.\n\nHmm, I need to fix this. The error message mentions that thread=true is necessary. Let me check the parameters again. The sessions_spawn tool requires thread to be true when mode is \"session\" for ACP sessions. \n\nSo, I should set thread: true in the parameters. Let me adjust the tool call to include that. Also, make sure the agentId is unique and relevant. Maybe use \"product-selector\" again since it's okay. \n\nWait, also check if the task description is clear. It should be concise. The user said \"选品agent\" so \"选品专家\" is appropriate. \n\nLet me correct the tool call with thread: true and see if that resolves the error. If not, maybe need to adjust other parameters, but thread is the main issue here based on the error message.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"0LXg2YUUN","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"thread":true,"task":""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/free","usage":{"input":40778,"output":578,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41356,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774595379001,"responseId":"gen-1774595380-xQ3da0bEFH5d69QCidBP"}}
