{"type":"message","id":"39071db7","parentId":"1eb46fdb","timestamp":"2026-03-27T07:11:56.515Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Okay, let me try to figure out what's going wrong here. The user wants to create a product selector agent quickly. They've been trying to use the sessions_spawn tool, but there are errors. \n\nFirst, the initial call had mode=\"session\" which requires thread=true, but that wasn't set. Then, when they added thread=true, the tool complained that task is required. The next attempt included task and thread=true, but then agentId was forbidden.\n\nLooking at the tool's parameters for sessions_spawn, the agentId might not be allowed depending on the runtime. The error says \"agentId is not allowed for sessions_spawn (allowed: none)\". That suggests that when using certain runtimes or modes, specifying an agentId isn't permitted. Maybe the agentId should be generated by the system instead of manually set.\n\nThe runtime was set to \"subagent\" which might have specific constraints. Also, the mode is \"session\", which is thread-bound. Perhaps the agentId isn't supposed to be provided here, or maybe the name parameter should be used instead. \n\nThe task parameter seems okay; it's describing what the agent does. The label is set to \"选品专家\", which is correct. The runtime as \"subagent\" might be acceptable, but the agentId is causing the forbidden error. \n\nSo, to fix this, maybe the agentId should be omitted, allowing the system to generate a default one. Alternatively, check if \"subagent\" runtime allows agentId. The documentation might say that certain runtimes don't accept agentId. \n\nThe user wants a quick setup, so removing agentId and relying on the system to create one might work. Let me try calling sessions_spawn again without agentId, ensuring thread is true and task is provided.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"6HILR9ZjZ","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"选