{"type":"message","id":"38f0cfa1","parentId":"35ef9cf6","timestamp":"2026-03-27T07:13:56.465Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Okay, let me try to figure out what's going wrong here. The user wants to create a sub-agent for product selection, and I'm using the sessions_spawn tool to do that. But every time I call it, there's an error. Let me check the tool's parameters and the errors I'm getting.\n\nFirst, the user mentioned that the agentId isn't allowed for sessions_spawn. The tool's description says that agentId should only be used if the runtime is \"acp\" and the default agent isn't configured. Since the user is creating a sub-agent, maybe agentId isn't necessary here. So I should remove agentId from the arguments.\n\nNext, the runtime parameter was set to \"subagent, \" with a space, which is invalid. The runtime must be exactly \"subagent\" or \"acp\". The comma at the end might be causing a syntax error. I need to correct that to \"subagent\".\n\nThe mode was set to \"session\", but the error says that mode=\"session\" requires thread=true. The user did set thread=true in later attempts, but maybe there's an issue with how the parameters are structured. Let me check the tool's required parameters. The sessions_spawn tool requires \"task\" and might need other parameters. Wait, looking back, the tool's required parameters are [\"task\"], so task is mandatory. The user provided that, but maybe there are validation issues with other fields.\n\nThe error about runtime needing to be one of the allowed values is critical. The runtime must be either \"subagent\" or \"acp\". The previous attempt had \"subagent, \" with a space, which is invalid. So correct that to \"subagent\".\n\nAlso, the thread parameter was set to true, which is required for mode=\"session\". But the error says thread=true is unavailable because there's no plugin for subagent spawning hooks. That's a dependency issue. The system might not support threads for sub-agents in this context. Maybe the user's setup doesn't allow threads, so using mode=\"session\" with thread=true isn't possible. In that case, perhaps using mode=\"run\" instead of \"session\" would work, even though it's a one-shot task.\n\nPutting it all together: the correct call should have runtime as \"subagent\", thread=true, and remove agentId. Also, ensure the task description is properly formatted without any syntax errors. Let me try that.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"TFaLaqYoH","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"选品专家，负责快速选品、市场调研、竞品分析，能够评估产品潜力和市场价值","label":"选品专家","mode":"session","runtime":"subagent, "}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/free","usage":{"input":41554,"output":1171,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42725,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774595553604,"responseId":"gen-1774595555-hXnZp57f6ebXXwwoszgN"}}
